.TH GUIX "1" "January 2026" "GNU" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
guix \- manual page for guix style (GNU Guix) 1.5.0rc1.47-fc2f5a
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B guix
\fI\,style \/\fR[\fI\,OPTION\/\fR]... [\fI\,PACKAGE\/\fR]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
Update package definitions to the latest style.
.TP
\fB\-S\fR, \fB\-\-styling\fR=\fI\,RULE\/\fR
apply RULE, a styling rule
.TP
\fB\-l\fR, \fB\-\-list\-stylings\fR
display the list of available style rules
.TP
\fB\-n\fR, \fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
display files that would be edited but do nothing
.TP
\fB\-L\fR, \fB\-\-load\-path\fR=\fI\,DIR\/\fR
prepend DIR to the package module search path
.TP
\fB\-e\fR, \fB\-\-expression\fR=\fI\,EXPR\/\fR
consider the package EXPR evaluates to
.TP
\fB\-\-input\-simplification\fR=\fI\,POLICY\/\fR
follow POLICY for package input simplification, one
of 'silent', 'safe', or 'always'
.TP
\fB\-f\fR, \fB\-\-whole\-file\fR
format the entire contents of the given file(s)
.TP
\fB\-A\fR, \fB\-\-alphabetical\-sort\fR
place the contents in alphabetical order as well
.TP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
display this help and exit
.TP
\fB\-V\fR, \fB\-\-version\fR
display version information and exit
